Rating: 4
Very important to make sure you use a good red wine when making this recipe. The flavor of the wine is front and center and if you use a cheap cooking wine that you don't particularly like the taste of, it will affect how the flavor of the gravy turns out. If you are short on time, you can substitute frozen meatballs instead of making your own. The first time we made this, it was perfect! The second time we made this, we used a different wine which really impacted the flavor of the gravy. So I used sun-dried tomato paste instead of regular tomato paste, add red pepper flakes to taste, and used some Bisto (British Brown Gravy Mix) to round the flavor out. Just delicious!! We had pasta with the meatballs but you could use mashed potatoes or polenta instead. We also like to put the meatballs and gravy on a bed of lettuce and spinach.

