Rating: 4
Sooooo good! I was skeptical about the method but after making this recipe several times, I decided the reason the recipe specifies baking the meatballs first is that processing the meat mixture results in a very tender meatball that is susceptible to breaking during sauteeing. Baking the meatballs prior to browning seems to give them more structure. I used a sieve to dust the meatballs with flour, turning them with a spatula to coat them evenly. I found the flavor of this dish was enhanced when I prepared the meatballs the day before I planned to eat them, refrigerating them overnight in the gravy. This meal is particularly delicious prepared with the Mashed Potatoes with Spinach and Cheese. Oh, yum!

