I really liked this recipe; it was a little salty, though. Because I had no summer savory on hand, I used oregano and less pepper. They came out soft, as meatballs should be; otherwise, they would be little hamburgers. My guests loved it. "Mmmmm" was their reaction.

Rating: 3
After reading the reviews of other cooks on this one, I decreased the bread slightly and increased the tomato paste slightly and they were very , very good. The spinach mashed potoaoes went wonderfully with them. Great comfort food.

Rating: 4
I made this recipe and very much enjoyed it, but agreed with others that it could have been even better. I pulled back on the amount of bread which I think helped the meatballs be more like meatballs as opposed to round meatloafs. I cooked them in the skillet about 10 to 15 minutes, which gave them more a crisp outer edge. After removing the meatballs, I sauted half a shallot (diced) and garlic clove (diced). Then added the meatballs and wine mixture. I doubled the paste, which helped to thiken the sauce. After adding the beef broth, I simmered for 20 to 25 minutes (add broth if gets too thick). I also cut this recipe in half. My family and I thought the results were fabulous. I will definitely make this dish again. Excellent.

Rating: 3
I liked this dish a lot. I followed the recipe as written and found the sauce to be well-flavored. I thought the red wine, beef stock and tomato paste had enough zip on their own.

Rating: 3
I agree with other reviewers that the sauce needed something. Maybe less wine. Meatballs were very good, though. My family liked the dish, but not as much as the leftover meatballs the next day in sandwiches. Now that was great!

Rating: 4
My husband and I really loved this dish. I would suggest cutting the bread into smaller pieces before putting it in the food processor. Will definately make again.

Rating: 3
i liked this a lot, and my meat-and-potatoes friends *loved* it, although i was worried because the reviews seemed so mixed. i skipped the step of frying the already-baked meatballs in a skillet, they were so tasty already i didn't think they needed a butter-bath to improve them. i cut by nearly half the beef broth the recipe calls for, so the gravy was thickier and wine-ier.

Rating: 4
I have already made these meatballs twice. I added 4 cloves of minced garlic to the meat mixture and that kicked it up. Served them with garlic mashed potatoes - yummy! I have other meatball recipes that I also make, and this one will be a keeper too!

