Rating: 3
My family liked the gravy. This was great with mashed potatoes and a green salad. We'll make it again!

Rating: 2
This recipe took quite a bit of tweaking. I found the gravy bland so added garlic and sauted mushrooms. The meatballs had too much bread in them, I'm going to cut it down to a half or third of the amount called for. Also added some worcestershire sauce to the gravy, about a teaspoon.

Rating: 1
More like meat loaf balls. Too much bread filling. Sauce was mediocre.

Rating: 1
This was not something I would make again. The sauce just tasted like salty beef broth. There are so many wonderful recipes I have tried and saved but this one doesn't make the cut.

Rating: 3
My husband made this for dinner and I didn't believe him when he said he mixed the ingredients in a food processor until I read the receipe in the magazine. The meatballs were flavorful and light much like my Mom used to make. I made them and gave the dish a mediterranean twist by substituting 1 tsp ground roasted cumin seeds for the summer savory and served them over orzo.